bib_record.title: Elastic and inelastic proton scattering on Si29

free_txt: The energy resolution of the beam was approximately
200 eV. The proton energy was calibrated by use of the
Al27(p,g)Si28 reaction as the reference point.
The targets were prepared by evaporating SiO2,
enriched in Si29 onto 10-mu-g/cm2-thick carbon foils
for the elastic scattering measurements and onto
cooling disks for the inelastic scattering.

The yield of inelastically scattered protons from
Si29 was obtained by measuring the yield of the
1.273-MeV gamma ray from the first excited state of
barrier detectors placed at angles of 90, 130, 140 and
150 degrees with respect to the beam direction and at
a distance of 10 cm from the target. The dectectors
have a 50-mm2 sensitive area and 25-keV resolution.
